Adds a sync or async task to the queue. Always returns a promise.

comment.returns: A promise that resolves when all functions are resolved.

comment.shortText: Clear the queue.
Can be called multiple times. Useful if you for example add additional items at a later time.
comment.returns: A promise that settles when the queue becomes empty.

comment.shortText: The difference with `.onEmpty` is that `.onIdle` guarantees that all work from the queue has finished. `.onEmpty` merely signals that the queue is empty, but it could mean that some promises haven't completed yet.
comment.returns: A promise that settles when the queue becomes empty, and all promises have completed; `queue.size === 0 && queue.pending === 0`.

comment.shortText: Put queue execution on hold.
Size of the queue, filtered by the given options.
comment.text: For example, this can be used to find the number of items remaining in the queue with a specific priority level.

comment.shortText: Start (or resume) executing enqueued tasks within concurrency limit. No need to call this if queue is not paused (via `options.autoStart = false` or by `.pause()` method.)
Priority of operation. Operations with greater priority will be scheduled first.
Whether queue tasks within concurrency limit, are auto-executed as soon as they're added.
Whether the task must finish in the given interval or will be carried over into the next interval count.
Concurrency limit.
The length of time in milliseconds before the interval count resets. Must be finite.
The max number of runs in the given interval of time.
Class with a `enqueue` and `dequeue` method, and a `size` getter. See the [Custom QueueClass](https://github.com/sindresorhus/p-queue#custom-queueclass) section.
Whether or not a timeout is considered an exception.
Per-operation timeout in milliseconds. Operations fulfill once `timeout` elapses if they haven't already.
